on Complaint Portal\nStudents Counsellings Centre\nHome\nExamination\nAbout\nMenu\nAbout\nResults\nPh.D Award Notification\nExamination Notices\nGuidelines/Rules/Regulations\nForm Formats\nExam Related Circular & Notices\nCOE Functions\nOffice Staff\nProf. Vikram Singh Yadav\nController of Examination\nE-mail:\ncoe@bbau.ac.in\nTenure of Controller of Examination\nThe Examination Section is the backbone of the University system through which both entry and exit of the students are ensured. Conduct of examinations and declaration of results are the most important activities of the examination section.\nThe section involves in pre-examination works (issue of roll No./admit cards, question papers setting, issue of answerbooks), examinations works (supply of question papers), and post examination works (verification and declaration of results, tabulation/grade entries, issue of gradesheets, to resolve issues of UFM’s/grievances). In addition to the above, the section involves in M.Phil./Ph.D. related evaluation/viva activities and award of degrees. It also involves in issue of various certificates like transcript/provisional degree/migration/first rank certificates, etc. and conduct of convocations.\nThe Examination Section is headed by Controllor of Examinations and having a team of officers and staff to look after the examination related works.'),(306,'Proctor','See content','Not Available','prof.chandrabbau@gmail.com','https://www.bbau.ac.in/Proctor.aspx','Proctor\nDean Student Welfare\nResearch & Development\nDirector IQAC\nHindi Cell\nLibrarian\nDean Academic affairs\nAlumni Cell\nChief Vigilance Officer\nDeans of School\nHeads of Department\nOther / Important Centre\'s\nAcademics\nAcademics\nDean Academic Affairs\nM.Phil / Ph.D Regulations\nMOU\nConsultancy\nCourse folder\nAcademic Calender\nHolidays\nInstitutional Academic Integrity Panel (IAIP)\nCentre for Industry Institution Partnership Program (CIIPP)\nIQAC\nAbout\nIQAC\nAcademic Flexibility\nFoundation Course