ucture\nUniversity Sophisticated Instrumentation Centre (USIC)\nLibrary\nHostel\'s\nHealth Centre\nMedia Centre\nGuest House\nSports\nAuditorium\nAtal Bihari Vajpayee Auditorium & Conference Hall\'s\nIT Infrastructure\nUniversity Computer Centre\nNational Knowledge Network\nStudents\nCentral Placement Cell\nInformation Guidance Bureau\nResidential Coaching Academy\nRemedial Coaching Program\nDr. Ambedkar Centre of Excellence\nOthers\nProcedures and policies\nBasic Facility for Women\nPost Office\nBank\nATM\nLogin\nLogin\nInternet User Authentication\nEmail (@bbau.ac.in)\nExam Section (ERP)\nWebex Login\nPortals\nSamarth Students Login\nUGC Grievance Redressal Portal\nStudents Feedback Form\nSC/ST, OBC, Disable & Minority Discrimination Complaint Portal\nStudents Counsellings Centre\nHome\nProctor\nAbout\nMenu\nAbout\nProctorial Board\nAnti-Ragging Committee\nProctorial Board Satellite Centre, Amethi\nSecurity Officer\nCirculars/Orders\nStudent Grievance Details\nCode of Conduct\nGallery\nProf. Ram Chandra\nProctor\nPhone: +91 - 9450652324\nE-mail:\nprof.chandrabbau@gmail.com\nDr. Sushil Kumar Pandey\nDeputy Proctor (Satellite Center Amethi)\nPhone: +91 - 9005516024\nE-mail:\ndr.sushilpandey@gmail.com\nBabasaheb Bhimrao Ambedkar University (A Central University) established the office of Proctor under the provision of its act 1994,\nwhich came into force from 10.01.1996. The proctor is a statutory officer of the University and head of the Proctorial board.\nThe major objectives of Proctorial board are enforcing discipline and controlling law and orders of student community.\nThe Proctor office comprises Proctorial board, anti ragging committee, anti ragging squad and anti ragging cell as the major\ncommittee to control the different sphere of discipline. The office of proctor constituted three tier organizations i.e. proctorial\nboard with Dy. Proctor, Asst. proctors & members, while at second tier security officer and at third tier the outsourced ex-army men\nas security staff with supervisor guards and chowkidars. The University has two campus i.e. main campus at Lucknow and satellite campus\nat Amethi. The office of proctor has to ensure discipline for maintaining law and order and total security to both campus of University.'),(307,'Dean Student Welfare','See content','Not Available','Not Available','https://www.bbau.ac.in/DeanStudentWelfare.aspx','Dean Student Welfare\nAlumni\nFaculty\nSocial Initiative\nCareer\ne-Learning\nAccreditation\nAchievements\nLibrary\nCampus Ambience\nBBAU ERP: Samarth\n????? ???????\nSitemap\nBabasaheb Bhimrao Ambedkar University, Lucknow\n????????? ?????? ???????? ?????????????\nBabasaheb Bhimrao Ambedkar University\n( A Central University )\nAccredited \'A++\' Grade by NAAC (2023)\nNIRF Ranked 37\nISO 14001:2015\nAbout\nAbout\nUniversity\nVision & Mission\nAct & Statutes\nAcademic Ordinance\nPublic Self Disclosure\nKulgeet\nContact\nUniversity Gallery\'s\nEvent Gallery\nPress/Media Gallery\nVideo Gallery\nAdministration\nStatutory Bodies\nBoard of Management\nAcademic Council\nPlanning Board\nFinance Committee\nAdministration\nVisitor\nChancellor\nVice Chancellor\nOmbudsman\nRegistrar\nFinance Officer\nController Of Examination\nProctor\nDean Student Welfare\nResearch & Development\nDirector IQAC\nHindi Cell\nLibrarian\nDean Academic affairs\nAlumni Cell\nChief Vigilance Officer\nDeans of School\nHeads of Department\nOther / Important Centre\'s\nAcademics\nAcademics\nDean Academic Affairs\nM.Phil / Ph.D Regulations\nMOU\nConsultancy\nCourse folder\nAcademic Calender\nHolidays\nInstitutional Academic Integrity Panel (IAIP)\nCentre for Industry Institution Partnership Program (CIIPP)\nIQAC\nAbout\nIQAC\nAcademic Flexibility\nFoundation Course\nChoice Based Credit System\nPublications\nAnnual Reports\nBBAU Newsletter\nJournals\nIQAC\nSchool & Dept.\nSchool\nAmbedkar School of Social Sciences\nLife Sciences\nInformation Science & Technology\nEarth & Environmental Sciences\nEducation\nHome Science\