owledge Network\nStudents\nCentral Placement Cell\nInformation Guidance Bureau\nResidential Coaching Academy\nRemedial Coaching Program\nDr. Ambedkar Centre of Excellence\nOthers\nProcedures and policies\nBasic Facility for Women\nPost Office\nBank\nATM\nLogin\nLogin\nInternet User Authentication\nEmail (@bbau.ac.in)\nExam Section (ERP)\nWebex Login\nPortals\nSamarth Students Login\nUGC Grievance Redressal Portal\nStudents Feedback Form\nSC/ST, OBC, Disable & Minority Discrimination Complaint Portal\nStudents Counsellings Centre\nHome\nStudent\'s Welfare\nDean\nDocuments\nOffice Staff\nActivity\nProf. Narendra Kumar\nDean, Student\'s Welfare\nIt is a matter of great pleasure to welcome all new young and vibrant knowledge seekers to the NAAC Accredited “A” Grade Central University. It gives me immense pleasure to welcome on campus all newcomers joining different academic programme of the university and I hope that some of them will become wards of our hostels.\nOf late the university has attracted candidates from different parts of the country and the Globe. We have 06 hostels to accommodate outstation candidates on the campus. The well staffed hostels are equipped with mess, well equipped recreation room, reading room and opportunities for curricular and co-curricular activities. Each hostel has an Administrative Warden and Warden (s) to look after various activities in the hostel premises. The girl hostels have matrons round the clock. The vibrant hostels, thus, provide a comfortable stay and good ambience to the inmates for their scholastic pursuits\nThis brochure provides all the basic and necessary information which will ensure each ward a smooth and enjoyable life. There is a well constituted DSW team headed by DSW with two Dy. DSWs, one each for girls and boys hostels. In addition, the team has two cultural Asstt. DSWs, two maintenance Asstt. DSWs and two allotment Asstt. DSWs. We have a full-fledged team of Proctorial office headed by Prof. Sanjay Kumar as Proctor.\nHence, it shall be our collective efforts to make your stay in the university comfortable, while at the same instance we shall expect each ward to follow the disciplinary norms laid down by the university and conduct themselves with decency and decorum. The complete machinery of the DSW section is for the welfare of the students and they should feel free to access this Office as and when required. We shall do our best to provide assistance and advice as per their need and requirement.'),(308,'Research & Development','See content','Not Available','shishir.cs@bbau.ac.in','https://www.bbau.ac.in/ResearchDevelopment.aspx','Research & Development\nDirector IQAC\nHindi Cell\nLibrarian\nDean Academic affairs\nAlumni Cell\nChief Vigilance Officer\nDeans of School\nHeads of Department\nOther / Important Centre\'s\nAcademics\nAcademics\nDean Academic Affairs\nM.Phil / Ph.D Regulations\nMOU\nConsultancy\nCourse folder\nAcademic Calender\nHolidays\nInstitutional Academic Integrity Panel (IAIP)\nCentre for Industry Institution Partnership Program (CIIPP)\nIQAC\nAbout\nIQAC\nAcademic Flexibility\nFoundation Course\nChoice Based Credit System\nPublications\nAnnual Reports\nBBAU Newsletter\nJournals\nIQAC\nSchool & Dept.\nSchool\nAmbedkar School of Social Sciences\nLife Sciences\nInformation Science & Technology\nEarth & Environmental Sciences\nEducation\nHome Science\nLegal Studies\nManagement and Commerce\nPhysical & Decision Sciences\nLanguages and Literature\nMedia and Communication\nAgricultural Sciences & Technology\nPharmaceutical Sciences\nSanskrit & Indic Studies\nSchool of Vocational & Futuristic Studies\nSchool of Yoga Naturopathy & Cognitive Studies\nSchool of Performing Arts\nSchool of Engineering & Technology\nCentre\'s & Institute\nSatellite Centre, Amethi\nUniversity Institute of Engineering & Technology\nOther / Important Centre\'s\nProgramme\nDoctoral\nPh.D\nM.Phil\nIntegrated Courses\nB.Sc.-M.Sc\nBBA-LLB\nPost Graduate\nM.Sc..\nM.Tech..\nM.A...\nLLM\nM.Ph