 Form\nSC/ST, OBC, Disable & Minority Discrimination Complaint Portal\nStudents Counsellings Centre\nHome\nChief Vigilance Officer\nProf. Raees Ahmad Khan\nChief Vigilance Officer\nPhone: +91-9305352751\nE-mail:\nkhanraees@yahoo.com\nBabasaheb Bhimrao Ambedkar University has appointed a CVO as per rules of UGC , Government of India to keep a close watch on official work so that it does not indulge in acts of corruption.\nProf. Raees Ahmad Khan is working as the Chief Vigilance Officer (C.V.O) of University.\nThe CVO is mainly responsible for the prevention and detection of corruption cases in the University and also for taking legal action wherever necessary. The CVO is to further ensure the following:\nMaintaining proper surveillance on officers of doubtful integrity.\nEnsure prompt observance of Conduct Rules relating to integrity\nLocation of sensitive spots, regular and surprise inspections of such spots and proper scrutiny of personnel who are posted in sensitive posts.\nIntroduction of preventive measures for bringing transparency and simplicity in the process of allocation and disbursement of grants to different sections and department\nCVO also observe Vigilance Awareness Week as per the instructions issued by the CVC.\nS.N.\nSubject/ Download\n1.\nHandbook on Vigilance Awareness was released by the Hon\'ble Vice Chancellor on 29th October 2025'),(315,'Deans Of Schools','See content','+91-7376762753','shuradarapuri@gmail.com','https://www.bbau.ac.in/DeansofSchools.aspx','Deans of Schools\nAlumni\nFaculty\nSocial Initiative\nCareer\ne-Learning\nAccreditation\nAchievements\nLibrary\nCampus Ambience\nBBAU ERP: Samarth\n????? ???????\nSitemap\nBabasaheb Bhimrao Ambedkar University, Lucknow\n????????? ?????? ???????? ?????????????\nBabasaheb Bhimrao Ambedkar University\n( A Central University )\nAccredited \'A++\' Grade by NAAC (2023)\nNIRF Ranked 37\nISO 14001:2015\nAbout\nAbout\nUniversity\nVision & Mission\nAct & Statutes\nAcademic Ordinance\nPublic Self Discl